        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued August 1 at 3:47PM MDT by NWS Denver CO</headline>
        <description>At 347 PM MDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 5
miles north of Bennett, or 28 miles east of Denver, moving north at
15 mph.

HAZARD...Landspouts, wind gusts up to 50 mph, and pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Minor damage to outdoor objects is possible. Gusty winds
could knock down tree limbs and blow around unsecured objects.

Locations impacted include...
Eastern Aurora and Bennett.
</description>
        <instruction>Monitor the weather situation closely and be alert for threatening
weather conditions.

If a tornado is spotted seek shelter inside a sturdy building.</instruction>
